In this example, using Numba was faster than Cython. Numba can also be used to write vectorized functions that do not require the user to explicitly loop over the observations of a vector; a vectorized function will be applied to each row automatically. Consider the following example of doubling each observation:

```
import numba
def double_every_value_nonumba(x):
return x * 2
@numba.vectorize
def double_every_value_withnumba(x): # noqa E501
return x * 2
